other_tests.findings: A simple appearing cyst in the lower pole of the left kidney measures 3.2 cm. There is no hydronephrosis or stones bilaterally. Normal cortical echogenicity and corticomedullary differentiation are seen bilaterally. Right kidney: 10.0 cm, Left kidney: 9.7 cm. The bladder is only minimally distended and cannot be fully assessed on the current study.
